http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/Officials-get-cracking-on-Greenfield-airport-project-survey/article13983731.ece

The ambitious proposal for setting up a Greenfield airport at the coal town of Kothagudem received yet another fillip with a team of officials from the Rail India Technical and Economic Service (RITES) on Tuesday launching a fortnight-long comprehensive survey in Kothagudem constituency on the much awaited airport project.The State Government has already approved the pre-feasibility report prepared by a team of technical experts from the RITES last year and urged the public sector company to proceed with the next stage of the project, the sources said.Meanwhile, a four-member team from RITES called on Kothagudem MLA Jalagam Venkat Rao in the coal town on Tuesday.Mr. Rao apprised the team members of the air passenger traffic potential of the coal hub, strategically located in the vast industrial corridor dotted with a host of major industries, including the Singareni Collieries Company Limited with its headquarters in Kothagudem, Heavy Water Plant in Manuguru and KTPS in Palvancha, sources said.He made specific mention of the historic Sri Sitaramachandra Swamy temple in Bhadrachalam, situated nearly 40 kms from Kothagudem, and the vibrant tourism potential of the sprawling Kinnerasani wildlife sanctuary in Palvancha mandal, besides other major tourist destinations nearby the coal town.